Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 1fc213594ad32ef5d47bc26bd4e8b54b50c3dc6c
The couple of symlinks I looked at all seem to be referencing hard-coded path /home/ed. That doesn't seem correct to me. I would expect it to be relative to the git clone path.
Yep, that was unintentional.  I was trying to script some things for making sure we only got the selected symlinks, and messed it up.  I've fixed the patchset to be correct now.
Should the symlink be relative path or be referencing $HOME or ~?
They should be relative.  Fixed.
This gets updated when scripts/update_schemas.py is ran?
nope.  the hope is that people can update these in their patchsets.  if you need a new schema. you just symlink it here, and the rest just works.
Do we need any documentation for this? I think using new schemas have slowed down but it still happens

We didn't document the old way and folks figured it out, so idk.  I'm somewhat hoping to get all this stuff organized, so we can have a more holistic documentation in OEM_SCHEMAS.md and have a path for folks to upstream OEM implementations if they want to, and schema installation is one thing holding us back from that (all systems have to ship all schemas today).  I suspect the "symlink into the folder" is just a stepping stone along the path to getting there.

If you want documentation, I can write some, but I really wouldn't expect that anyone read it.
Could add documentation after
